@inherits LayoutComponentBase

@*
    Editorial two-column shell:
      - left  = fixed 280px sidebar (NavMenu) with a faint dotted texture
      - right = main content area; pages own their own padding so the title
                can hug a chosen rhythm.

    No top "About" link, no Bootstrap container. Layout is plain Tailwind utilities.

    Responsive (issue #10): below the `md` breakpoint the two columns stack —
    the sidebar becomes a full-width top strip (dropping its fixed 280px width
    that would otherwise eat most of a 390px phone viewport and force the page
    to overflow horizontally) and the main content takes the full width beneath
    it. At `md`+ the original fixed-sidebar row layout is restored.
*@

<div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row min-h-screen bg-cream text-ink">
    <aside class="w-full md:w-[280px] shrink-0 border-b md:border-b-0 md:border-r border-line bg-surface calee-sidebar-texture">
        <NavMenu />
    </aside>

    <main class="flex-1 min-w-0">
        @Body
    </main>
</div>
